shodan commands and use example:

🔎 Basic Search Queries

These are simple keywords you can type directly:

apache → Finds servers running Apache
nginx → Nginx web servers
webcam → Publicly exposed cameras
ftp → FTP servers

🎯 Common Filters (Core Power of Shodan)
🌍 Targeting Hosts
ip:192.168.1.1 → Specific IP
net:192.168.0.0/16 → CIDR range
hostname:example.com → Domain

🌐 Services & Ports
port:22 → SSH
port:3389 → RDP
port:21 → FTP

🖥️ OS & Software
os:windows
product:Apache
version:2.4.49

📍 Location-Based
country:eg → .....
city:....

🏢 Organization / ISP
org:name
isp:name

LIVE:
site:gov.in intext:"password"
filetype:xls inurl:"email"
intitle:"index of" "backup"
intitle:"index of" identity card

⚡ Popular “Dork”-Style Queries

These combine filters to find interesting/exposed systems:

port:23 "login" → Telnet login prompts
port:3306 mysql → MySQL databases
port:6379 redis → Redis instances (often unsecured)
port:9200 elasticsearch → Elasticsearch servers
port:27017 mongodb → MongoDB databases

📷 IoT / Camera Searches
webcamXP
product:Hikvision
title:"IP Camera"

🔐 Security / Vulnerability Hunting
ssl.cert.subject.cn:example.com
http.title:"Index of /" → Open directories
http.html:"password"
vuln:CVE-2021-44228 → Log4Shell

🧠 Advanced Filters
has_screenshot:true → Devices with screenshots
http.status:200 → Only successful HTTP responses
before:2024-01-01 / after:2023-01-01 → Time filtering

💻 CLI (Command Line Interface)

If you're using the Shodan CLI:

Install
pip install shodan
Init
shodan init YOUR_API_KEY
Search
shodan search apache
Get Host Info
shodan host 8.8.8.8
Download Results
shodan download results apache

